The Lagos state government has confirmed four additional Coronavirus (Covid-19) cases, bringing the total confirmed cases in the state to 29. The commissioner for health, Prof. Akin Abayomi, who disclosed this via his twitter handle said “The total confirmed cases in Lagos as at 1.10pm today 24th March, 2020 is 29.” Abayomi said one of the confirmed cases attended the African Magic viewers’ Choice Award (AMVCA) held on the 14th of March at Eko Hotels. He said, “I hereby notify all participants at the African Magic viewers’ Choice Award (AMVCA) held on 14th March at Eko Hotels that they may have come in contact with one of the confirmed cases in Lagos and are most likely to have been exposed to COVID-19 Infection.” He appealed to Attendees at the said event to observe strict self-isolation and to call the Toll-Free line 08000corona if they notice any of the COVID-19 related symptoms. He however urged all Nigerians to take responsibility by practicing Social Distancing to prevent the spread of the virus. 